e the release of what was to be his final film, Rio Lobo, Howard Hawks regaled a crowd with anecdotes and advice from almost 50 years in Hollywood. This interview was featured in our Spring 1971 issue. " class="ArticleCard__Outer-sc-zrtbni-0 eIZIIS articleCard false"><div class="ArticleCard__PageImageContainer-sc-zrtbni-5 ehvIXQ"><div class="ArticleCard__PageImage-sc-zrtbni-6 fNoWtw image"></div></div><h3 class="ArticleCard__Heading-sc-zrtbni-3 bynrVe">An audience with Howard Hawks</h3><div class="ArticleCard__Meta-sc-zrtbni-1 edgoES"><p class="ArticleCard__Author-sc-zrtbni-2 KIAzD">By Joseph McBride and Michael Wilmington</p></div><a href="https://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-and-sound/interviews/audience-howard-hawks-1971" title="Read An audience with Howard Hawks" class="ArticleCard__CallToAction-sc-zrtbni-4 fwpHHm"><span>An audience with Howard Hawks</span></a></article><article image48x27="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2022-03/jeanne-dielman-23-quai-du-commerce-1080-bruxelles-1975-delphine-seyrig-cooking-mince.jpg/96x54-cropped/jeanne-dielman-23-quai-du-commerce-1080-bruxelles-1975-delphine-seyrig-cooking-mince.jpg" imageAltText="" standfirst="In the 1970s, Chantal Akerman’s films found a new, personal way of screening women, as this feature from our November 1999 issue argues. " class="ArticleCard__Outer-sc-zrtbni-0 eIZIIS articleCard false"><div class="ArticleCard__PageImageContainer-sc-zrtbni-5 ehvIXQ"><div class="ArticleCard__PageImage-sc-zrtbni-6 gZdkjd image"></div></div><h3 class="ArticleCard__Heading-sc-zrtbni-3 bynrVe">Keeping a distance: Chantal Akerman’s Jeanne Dielman </h3><div class="ArticleCard__Meta-sc-zrtbni-1 edgoES"><p class="ArticleCard__Author-sc-zrtbni-2 KIAzD">By Janet Bergstrom</p></div><a href="https://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-and-sound/features/keeping-distance-chantal-akerman-jeanne-dielman" title="Read Keeping a distance: Chantal Akerman’s Jeanne Dielman " class="ArticleCard__CallToAction-sc-zrtbni-4 fwpHHm"><span>Keeping a distance: Chantal Akerman’s Jeanne Dielman </span></a></article><article image48x27="https://core-cms.bfi.org.uk/sites/default/files/styles/responsive/public/2021-05/moonlight-2016-boy-silhouetted-on-beach-at-sunset.jpg/96x54-cropped/moonlight-2016-boy-silhouetted-on-beach-at-sunset.jpg" imageAltText="" standfirst="Barry Jenkins discusses Moonlight, his by turns epic and intimate modern classic about a young gay man growing up against a backdrop of poverty, violence and drugs in Miami, in this conversation first published in our March 2017 issue." class="ArticleCard__Outer-sc-zrtbni-0 eIZIIS articleCard false"><div class="ArticleCard__PageImageContainer-sc-zrtbni-5 ehvIXQ"><div class="ArticleCard__PageImage-sc-zrtbni-6 OATjo image"></div></div><h3 class="ArticleCard__Heading-sc-zrtbni-3 bynrVe">Rhapsody in blue: Barry Jenkins on Moonlight</h3><div class="ArticleCard__Meta-sc-zrtbni-1 edgoES"><p class="ArticleCard__Author-sc-zrtbni-2 KIAzD">By Gaylene Gould</p></div><a href="https://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-and-sound/interviews/moonlight-barry-jenkins-2017-miami-oscar-winner" title="Read Rhapsody in blue: Barry Jenkins on Moonlight" class="ArticleCard__CallToAction-sc-zrtbni-4 fwpHHm"><span>Rhapsody in blue: Barry Jenkins on Moonlight</span></a></article></div><a href="https://www.bfi.org.uk/articles/category/from-the-sight-and-sound-archive" class="Button__PrimaryButton-sc-8dp7u4-0 iGKFPz ArticleGrid__CentredButton-sc-nctj0m-2 CtQWL">See all features from our archives</a></div><h2 aria-label="" class="Headline__H2-sc-e1fxl5-2 eKkqcD">Follow us on social media</h2><figure class="ImageSponsorLinks__Outer-sc-fogxlc-0 rZSof"><div class="ImageSponsorLinks__ImagesHolder-sc-fogxlc-1 enmboA"><div class="ImageSponsorLinks__ImageContainer-sc-fogxlc-2 kOZrxC"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/SightSoundmag" class="ImageSponsorLinks__Link-sc-fogxlc-3 brKMqi">children</a></div><div class="ImageSponsorLinks__ImageContainer-sc-fogxlc-2 kOZrxC"><a href="https://twi